new requirement: Meetings scheduled on Fridays must not start after 15:00. This requirement applies in addition to all previously described behavior. If a meeting would otherwise be valid but starts after 15:00 on a Friday, it must be excluded from the returned results. Update your solution, tests and documents to incorporate this requirement.

, For the development, consider the following specification:
 System Goal: To suggest all valid meeting start times within defined working hours that can accommodate a meeting of a given duration without overlapping any existing events.
 Inputs: to events
type: List [Dict [str, str]]
format: {"start": "HH:MM", "end": "HH:MM"}
valid values: start < end, use 24-hour time format
to meeting_duration
type: int
 Outputs: valid_slots
type: List [str]
to a list of meeting times in "HH:MM" 24-hour format
 Acceptance Criteria [{'ac_1': 'Given no existing events, when the meeting duration is 30 minutes on a Monday, then the earliest suggested slot is 09:00.', 'ac_2': 'Given there is a scheduled event from 14:00 to 15:20 when a 60-min. meeting is requested then no suggested meeting with start time interval', 'ac_3': 'Given scheduled event ends at 15:00 when 30-min. meeting requested then 15:30 is included as valid slot time', 'ac_6': 'Given the selected day is Friday when a meeting is required later than 15:00 then the start time is excluded from the suggested meeting slots'}]
 Constraints: [{'c_1': 'Fixed working hours (constraint)', 'c_2': 'Fixed time granularity (constraint)', 'c_3': 'No overlapping meetings (constraint)', 'c_4': 'Back-to-back meetings allowed (assumption)', 'c_5': 'Fixed lunch break (constraint)', 'c_6': 'Events are valid and well-formed (assumption)'}]
